UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304387895000283
KW  - R&D spillover
KW  - Firm level R&D
KW  - Firm level productivity
AB  - We test the R & D spillover hypothesis of the endogenous growth literature using panel data for a sample of private manufacturing firms in India over the period 1975–1986. We estimate an extended production function that includes the firm's own R & D capital stock and the spillover effect of the industry-wide R & D capital stock as inputs, as well as physical capital and labor hours. We specify models which eliminate three sources of estimation bias and flawed hypothesis tests: serially correlated errors, unobserved heterogeneity due to omitted factors of production, and endogenous determination of value-added and input levels. Several specification tests are used to select a well-behaved model. The final parameter estimates show evidence for the R & D spillover hypothesis in all industries.
ER  - 

